-- Zimbabwe’s Second-Largest City Bulawayo Eases Water Restrictions
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2013-02-08T09:19:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-08/zimbabwe-s-second-largest-city-bulawayo-eases-water-restrictions.html
Bulawayo, Zimbabwe’s biggest city
after Harare, plans to ease water rationing-restrictions after
better-than-expected rains fell in the southwest African nation,
Mayor  Thaba Moyo  said.  The cuts will be reduced to 72 hours a week starting Feb.
11 from 96 previously, Moyo said in phone interview from
Bulawayo.  More than 100 companies closed and 20,000 jobs were lost
because of the water crisis in Bulawayo, which has plagued the
city since 2010, the Harare-based  Standard  reported Oct. 14  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Marlborough, UK at 
